2026-05-07T23:58:42.027Z [+1794.59s] 🖥️ [/__saveUserData] DB3 updated, merged 518 games {"profile":"FamilyGuyBowling","fields":{"Name":"Family Guy Bowling","Developer":"Team Play","Publisher":"Team Play","Players":"1-8","Genre":"Sports, Bowling","Arcade Platform":"Team-Play PC Based","Interface":"Trackball","Tags":"","YouTube Link":"","Description":"In a bowling alley that feels like it could spiral into an episode at any moment, the Griffin family turns a simple match into a loud rivalry filled with one-liners and bad decisions. You pick your character, chase the perfect strike, and the tone can shift from fairly tame to much sharper depending on the cabinet settings. Between frames, video clips drop in like punchlines timed to keep the room laughing.","Metadata From":"Screenscraper.fr"}}
2026-05-07T23:59:40.647Z [+1853.21s] 🖥️ [/__saveUserData] DB3 updated, merged 518 games {"profile":"GoGoStrike","fields":{"Name":"Go Go Strike","Developer":"American Alpha","Publisher":"American Alpha","Players":"1","Genre":"Sports, Bowling","Arcade Platform":"PAOKAI Linux PC Based","Interface":"Trackball","Tags":"","YouTube Link":"","Description":"In a bowling alley setting, everything comes down to a string of throws where the goal is to stack strikes and avoid costly mistakes to push the score higher. Consistency matters, and a single late-frame ball can swing both the result and the payout. It's a video bowling redemption cabinet controlled with a trackball.","Metadata From":"Screenscraper.fr"}}
